---+!! User-based Evaluation of retrieval-based community question answering systems

*Purpose.* To investigate from users' perspective how a commonly used retrieval-based question answering system peforms compared to a modern neural semantic one, and more generally, what kind of results an information retrieval system should provide. All is evaluated on data from community question answering (cQA) platforms, namely various StackExchange sites.


*Required resources.* In Total 45 working hours. 30 subjects (students), each subject doing five tasks (scenarios), each task takes 5min (cutoff time 10min), plus three questionnaires per task results in ~15min per session and 75min for all sessions. Plus an introduction and follow-up questionnaire lead to ~90min per subject.
     
    
